Differential gene expression in snow crabs (Chionoecetes opilio) in response to different pH treatments

Courtney Skalley

2023-05-09

1 Introduction

This project contains a workflow for examining the effect of ocean acidification on gene expression of snow crabs. It runs using paired end RNA-Seq data prepared and provided by Laura Spencer. 63 juvenile crabs were exposed to the following pH treatments:

  • control (ambient)
  • pH 7.8 (8 hours)
  • pH 7.8 (12 weeks)
  • pH 7.5 (8 hours)
  • pH 7.5 (12 weeks)

After exposure, all crabs were sacrificed by puncturing the carapace through the cardiac region and preserved in RNA Later overnight at 4C prior to being transferred to -80C. All crabs sacrificed on 7/20/2021. mRNA samples were then extracted. Each of the 63 mRNA samples were run in both lanes of NovaSeq 6000, for a grand total of 126 paired-end RNA-Seq data sets. Sequence data received January 3, 2022.
